---
description: Component authoring rules
globs: ["packages/components/**/*.tsx", "registry/**/*.ts", "apps/storybook/**/*.tsx"]
---

Every component must:

1. Live in `packages/components/src/<kebab-case-name>.tsx`.
2. Have a matching manifest in `registry/ui/<kebab-case-name>.ts`.
3. Export named React symbols and compose the public API via `Object.assign` dot notation.
4. Have stories covering variants, states, RTL, and color mode (Storybook toolbar globals; see `15-stories-authoring.mdc`).
5. Have tests covering axe, interactions, and screen reader labels.
6. Support `asChild` where applicable through `@radix-ui/react-slot`.
7. Forward refs via `React.forwardRef`.
8. Accept `className` and compose through preset recipes.
9. Include `displayName` for devtools.
10. Stay fully typed. Do not use `any`.
11. Declare `lucide-react` only when the manifest actually needs it.
12. Keep user-facing strings localizable.
13. Document any `stalk.preset` manifest extensions required by installation.
14. Keep dot-notation namespaces tree-shakeable by building them from named exports.

Naming: source and manifest files use kebab-case; React exports use PascalCase.
